The Court of Appeal on Wednesday sacked the Senate Spokesman, Adedayo Adeyeye as the senator representing Ekiti South senatorial district in the upper chamber. Adeyeye, a former spokesman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) is a member of the All Progressives Congress (APC). The appellant court declared Senator Biodun Olujimi of the PDP winner of the election. Olujimi, a former principal officer in the 8th Senate, is a former Deputy Governor of Ekiti state. She had won the case at the lower tribunal in the state weeks back.